com.fortify.processrunner.cli

Class CLIOptionDefinitions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fortify.processrunner.cli.CLIOptionDefinitions

  • public class CLIOptionDefinitions
extends Object

    This class holds all configured CLIOptionDefinition instances. CLIOptionDefinition instances are indexed by name, group and optionally source. Name and group indexing speaks for itself, as name and group are CLIOptionDefinition properties. Source-based indexing allows for advanced updates to CLIOptionDefinition instances based on the components that provided each CLIOptionDefinition instance. For example, this is used by RunProcessRunnerFromSpringConfig.addCLIOptionDefinitions(CLIOptionDefinitions) to invoke IContextGenerator.updateProcessRunnerCLIOptionDefinitions(Collection) on CLIOptionDefinition instances that are solely provided by AbstractProcessRunner instances, excluding CLIOptionDefinition instances that were provided by the IContextGenerator instance. Other examples include adding extra information about which actions various options are related to, as can be seen in AbstractBugTrackerProcessRunner.

    Note that any CLIOptionDefinition instances being added to this CLIOptionDefinitions instances are being deep-copied before being stored; as such any updates to CLIOptionDefinition instances contained in this CLIOptionDefinitions instance will not affect the original CLIOptionDefinition instance.

    Author:
    Ruud Senden
